If VTK encounters a glTF *extension* it doesn't support, it warns that the
*extension* will be *ignored*. Furthermore, if it encounters an *image* with an
unexpected mime type, it *also* dispatches a warning.

However, the mime type may only exist in support of the extension that has
already been declared as "ignored". There are two problems with this:

1. It is logically inconsistent. Barking about images that only exist as part
   of an "ignored" extension is contradictory.
2. Drake provides a list of glTF extensions it supports (see
   RenderEngineVtkParams::gltf_extensions). Each listed extension, can be
   configured to *suppress* warnings about lack of support (we default to
   ignoring lack of support for KHR_texture_basisu). However, it works by
   focusing on a very specific message about glTF *extensions*. There is no
   simple way to change that mechanism to also account for other affiliated
   warning messages that might come through (i.e., the "unsupported mime type"
   warnings described above). But we *want* them suppressed.

The *proper* solution would be to modify VTK so that it is smart enough to
recognize the relationship between unsupported extension and other artifacts.
That is big and ugly. Instead, we simply remove the arbitrary per-image
warnings. The justification is as follows:

1. Generally, we expect the unsupported mime type to be related to an
   unsupported glTF extension. A warning for that has already been
   dispatched. We don't need any further warnings in this case.
2. It won't *fail* silently
   a. Obviously, if the image can be loaded, the warning doesn't get dispatched
      and removal of the warning has no bearing.
   b. If the image *can't* be loaded it is either
      i.  related to an unsupported extension (in which case it won't be used
          and the warning would be redundant), or
      ii. it is unaffiliated with any unsupported extension, which means when
          the scene is fully assembled, an error will be dispatched reporting
          the fact that the image couldn't be loaded. The error makes the
          warning mostly redundant.

Note: If someone were to disable Drake's default suppression of KHR_texture_basisu,
then the warning for the extension *would* be dispatched, but this patch means
we won't get per-image warnings for the images. As we have historically not
had these warnings, this constitutes a continuation of the status quo.

--- IO/Geometry/vtkGLTFDocumentLoader.cxx
+++ IO/Geometry/vtkGLTFDocumentLoader.cxx
@@ -913,8 +913,6 @@ bool vtkGLTFDocumentLoader::LoadImageData()
         // scene, an error will occur later when we attempt to render it. However, if it is not
         // used, there is no reason to fail the entire loading process just because we cannot read
         // an unused image.
-        vtkWarningMacro("No reader found for image with mime type '"
-          << image.MimeType << "' and uri '" << image.Uri << "'. Image will be set to null.");
         image.ImageData = nullptr;
         continue;
       }
